    <p>Over the course of his in­car­cer­a­tion, Daniel ex­pe­ri­enced a spir­i­tual trans­for­ma­tion and as­pires to join the clergy, but his crim­i­nal record means no sem­i­nary will ac­cept him. Sent to a re­mote vil­lage to work at a sawmill, a quick lie leads to him be­ing mis­taken for the town’s new priest. Though he has no train­ing, his pas­sion and charisma in­spire the com­mu­nity. At the same time, his un­con­ven­tional ser­mons and un­priestly be­hav­iour raise sus­pi­cions among some of the towns­folk. This award-win­ning film was nom­i­nated for Best In­ter­na­tional Fea­ture Film at this year’s Os­cars. It is the open­ing film for the Pol­ish Film Fes­ti­val hosted by in­die cin­ema The Pro­jec­tor.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The Pro­jec­tor, Level 5 Golden Mile Tower, 6001 Beach Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Ni­coll High­way WHEN: Till Wed AD­MIS­SION: $13.50</p>
    <p>INFO: the­p­ro­jec­tor.sg/ films-and-events/cor­pus-christi</p>


